The HTML Boilerplate: Understanding HTML structure
Boilerplate allows us to understand the structure of the html files
 - The HTML Boilerplate:
<!DOCTYPE html> # Tells any browser reading our html file that it's been written in version 5
<html lang="en"> # Actual html - root of the document
    <head> # Important info about Website, that's not displayed to the user is placed here.
        <meta charset="UTF-8"> # Ensures characters used in the website get displayed correctly
        <title>My Website</title> # Gets displayed in the tab bar of your browser
    </head> # Includes things that will help the website render in the browser correctly

    <body> # Content of website goes here
        <h1>Hello World!</h1>
    </body>
</html>
